div.p:
And, as Concerning those Fishings of England, Wales, and Ireland: Of their places: Yerely seasons: the many hundreds of forrein Fisherboats, yerely resorting: the diuers sort of fish, there taken: with the appertenances: I know right well, that (long ago
                  •
               ) all such matter, concerning these Fishings, is declared vnto some of the higher powers of this kingdom, and made manifest,R. H. by an other honest Ientleman of the Middle Temple. Who, very discretely and faithfully hath dealt there in, and still trauaileth, (and by diuers other wayes also) to farder the Weale-Publik of England, so much as in him lyeth.
